n-sued-by-brooklyn-employees-over-wage-theft-allegations-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAisha%20%26quot%3BPinky%26quot%3B%20Cole%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20the%20fast-food%20chain%20Slutty%20Vegan%20and%20the%20newest%20cast%20member%20of%20the%20coming%20season%20of%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-housewives-of-atlanta-stars-who-appreared-in-one-season-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EThe%20Real%20Housewives%20of%20Atlanta%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20on%20Thursday%20that%20%26quot%3Bbusiness%20debt%26quot%3B%20drove%20her%20to%20personal%20bankruptcy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETestifying%20under%20oath%20during%20a%20meeting%20of%20creditors%20in%20her%20bankruptcy%20case%2C%20the%2038-year-old%20entrepreneur%20said%20she%20had%20personally%20guaranteed%20much%20of%20her%20business's%20debt%2C%20prompting%20creditors%20to%20pursue%20her%20for%20repayment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20creditors%20were%20coming%20after%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Cole%2C%20who%20is%20set%20to%20star%20in%20Season%2017%20of%20%26quot%3BThe%20Real%20Housewives%20of%20Atlanta%26quot%3B%20next%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECole%20launched%20Slutty%20Vegan%20in%202018%20from%20a%20shared%20kitchen%20in%20Atlanta%2C%20before%20the%20business%20grew%20into%20more%20than%20a%20dozen%20brick-and-mortar%20locations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20its%20peak%2C%20the%20business%20%E2%80%94%20known%20for%20plant-based%20burgers%20like%20the%20%26quot%3BSloppy%20Toppy%26quot%3B%20or%20the%20%26quot%3BSuper%20Slut%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20was%20reportedly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fslutty-vegan-founder-pinky-no-business-plan-100-million-company-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eworth%20%24100%20million%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Though%20the%20business%20has%20faced%20financial%20struggles%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20several%20outposts%20still%20remain%20open.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20Thursday%20meeting%20of%20creditors%2C%20a%20federal%20bankruptcy%20trustee%20asked%20Cole%20how%20many%20bank%20accounts%20she%20currently%20had%2C%20to%20which%20she%20responded%2C%20%26quot%3Bpersonally%20none.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20actually%20just%20closed%20my%20personal%20bank%20account%20the%20day%20after%20retaining%20counsel.%20I%20was%20not%20aware%20that%20I%20needed%20to%20close%20my%20existing%20bank%20account%2C%26quot%3B%20Cole%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20account%20held%20about%20%246%20when%20it%20was%20closed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20if%20she%20had%20any%20source%20of%20income%2C%20Cole%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bnot%20personally%2C%26quot%3B%20before%20clarifying%20that%20she%20has%20multiple%20properties%20that%20she%20rents%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnder%20questioning%20from%20a%20representative%20of%20a%20South%20Carolina-based%20mortgage%20lender%2C%20Cole%20said%20she%20collects%20%241%2C500%20a%20month%20in%20rent%20from%20one%20Georgia%20property%20and%20%241%2C800%20a%20month%20from%20another.%20She%20added%20that%20she%20plans%20to%20lease%20another%20property%20beginning%20next%20month%20for%20%243%2C000%20a%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2286cb18d4-4799-4784-aa3d-f714a3287d50%5C%22%3EThree%20years%20of%20'missing'%20tax%20returns%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECole%20personally%20filed%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fcredit-score%2Fwhat-is-chapter-11-bankruptcy%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EChapter%2011%20bankruptcy%20protection%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20Georgia%20federal%20court%20last%20month%2C%20allowing%20her%20to%20reorganize%20her%20debts%20under%20court%20supervision%20in%20hopes%20of%20making%20them%20more%20manageable.%20Her%20filing%20estimated%20assets%20worth%20%241%20million%20to%20%2410%20million%20and%20estimated%20liabilities%20in%20the%20same%20range.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20handwritten%20bankruptcy%20petition%20shows%20that%20she%20owes%20%241.2%20million%20to%20the%20US%20Small%20Business%20Administration%20for%20an%20Economic%20Injury%20Disaster%20Loan%2C%20plus%20%24192%2C000%20in%20state%20taxes%20to%20the%20Georgia%20Department%20of%20Revenue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Cole%20initially%20filed%20for%20Chapter%2011%2C%20she%20did%20so%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bpro%20se%26quot%3B%20debtor%2C%20meaning%20she%20was%20not%20represented%20by%20a%20lawyer.%20But%20on%20Thursday%2C%20she%20told%20the%20trustee%20that%20she%20%26quot%3Bsoon%20realized%26quot%3B%20she%20needed%20an%20attorney%20and%20hired%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20actually%20working%20on%20amendments%20now%2C%20because%20I%20realized%20there's%20a%20lot%20of%20amendments%20that%20need%20to%20be%20made%2C%26quot%3B%20Cole%20told%20the%20trustee.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20creditors'%20meeting%2C%20Cole%20also%20faced%20questioning%20from%20an%20IRS%20official%20over%20three%20years%20of%20%26quot%3Bmissing%26quot%3B%20tax%20returns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20showing%20that%20you%20are%20missing%202020%2C%202023%2C%20and%202024%2C%20and%20we%20show%20that%20there%20is%20income%20for%20those%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20official%20said%2C%20requesting%20that%20those%20tax%20returns%20be%20filed%20%26quot%3Bpreferably%26quot%3B%20by%20the%20next%20creditors'%20meeting%20in%20mid-April.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECole's%20bankruptcy%20attorney%2C%20Jamie%20Christy%2C%20then%20told%20the%20official%20she%20would%20reach%20out%20to%20Cole's%20accountant%20%26quot%3Band%20see%20if%20we%20can%20figure%20this%20out%20before%20April%2017.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%20to%20Business%20Insider%2C%20Christy%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BWe%20will%20be%20amending%20her%20schedules.%20Until%20then%2C%20no%20other%20comments%20will%20be%20made.%20Ms.%20Cole%20has%20retained%20me%20to%20aid%20her%20in%20her%20bankruptcy%20and%20that%20is%20what%20I%20will%20do.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2215bb8acd-d04e-4106-96a3-1d9ffcca8979%5C%22%3ERapping%20about%20bankruptcy%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECole%20appears%20to%20be%20taking%20her%20Chapter%2011%20restructuring%20filing%20in%20stride.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20recent%20Instagram%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fpinkycole%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evideo%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Cole%20%E2%80%94%20dressed%20as%20children's%20educational%20YouTube%20star%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnetflix-signs-ms-rachel-creators-hollywood-merge-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMs.%20Rachel%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20broke%20down%20the%20bankruptcy%20process%20in%20a%20catchy%20rap%20set%20to%20the%20tune%20of%20Soulja%20Boy's%20%26quot%3BCrank%20That.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBankruptcy%20let's%20learn%20code%2C%20seven%20liquidate%20and%20roll%2C%2011%20you%20reorganize%2C%2013%20pay%20it%20back%20slow%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20sang.%20%26quot%3BNow%20watch%20me%20file%20that%20bankruptcy%2C%20file%20that%20bankruptcy%2C%20file%20that%20bankruptcy%2C%20file%20that%20bankruptcy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20Slutty%20Vegan%20entered%20a%20state-level%20restructuring%20process%20amid%20mounting%20debt%20that%20temporarily%20cost%20Cole%20ownership%20of%20the%20business%2C%20before%20she%20ultimately%20bought%20the%20brand%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20got%20to%20the%20point%20where%20I%20was%20paying%20%2480%2C000%20a%20week%20in%20payroll%20on%20my%20own.%20And%20I%20had%20to%20surrender%2C%26quot%3B%20Cole%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forbes.com%2Fsites%2Fcereal-entrepreneurs%2F2025%2F04%2F03%2Fhow-slutty-vegan-founder-pinky-cole-nearly-lost-her-business-forever%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%3C%2Fa%3E%20Forbes%20in%20a%202025%20interview.%20%26quot%3BSurrendering%20was%20the%20best%20thing%20that%20I%20could%20have%20ever%20done.%20Because%20what%20it%20taught%20me%20is%20that%20business%20is%20not%20a%20straight%20road%2C%20right%3F%20You're%20gonna%20get%20a%20flat%20tire%20here%20and%20there.%20But%20it's%20all%20about%20the%20bounce%20back%2C%20and%20I'm%20in%20my%20bounce%20back%20era.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-housewives-atlanta-pinky-cole-bankruptcy-slutty-vegan-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1773346938000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69b2f5ada96e437d6eb83820%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-housewives-atlanta-pinky-cole-bankruptcy-slutty-vegan-2026-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Slutty%20Vegan%20founder%20Aisha%20%26quot%3BPinky%26quot%3B%20Cole%20testified%20under%20oath%20Thursday%20that%20%26quot%3Bbusiness%20debt%26quot%3B%20led%20her%20to%20file%20for%20personal%20bankruptcy%20protection.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22nmusumeci%40businessinsider.com%20(Natalie%20Musumeci)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-housewives-atlanta-pinky-cole-bankruptcy-slutty-vegan-2026-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Nicole%20Kidman%20%E2%80%98Can%E2%80%99t%20Stand%20Bad%20Breath%E2%80%99%20and%20Told%20Alexander%20Skarsg%C3%A5rd%20to%20Stop%20Eating%20Falafel%20Before%20%E2%80%98Big%20Little%20Lies%E2%80%99%20Filming%3A%20%E2%80%98Not%20Before%20You%20Kiss%20or%20Make%20Love%E2%80%99%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1773346933000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1236686057%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Nicole%20Kidman%E2%80%99s%20interview%20on%20the%20%E2%80%9CLas%20Culturistas%E2%80%9D%20podcast%20gained%20traction%20on%20social%20media%20after%20the%20Oscar%20and%20Emmy%20winner%20revealed%20that%20she%20told%20Alexander%20Skarsg%C3%A5rd%20to%20stop%20eating%20falafel%20before%20their%20kissing%20scenes%20because%20of%20Kidman%E2%80%99s%20disdain%20for%20bad%20breath.%20%E2%80%9