her's%20nerves.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELet%20me%20tell%20you%3A%20You%20do%20%3Cem%3Enot%3C%2Fem%3E%20want%20your%20headphones%20to%20break%20while%20living%20with%20someone%20else%20in%20less%20than%2070%20square%20feet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20also%20have%20to%20juggle%20mundane%20but%20necessary%20planning%20for%20things%20like%20video-call%20acoustics%20when%20we%20both%20have%20work%20meetings%20at%20the%20same%20time.%20Sometimes%20I%20dream%20about%20a%20separate%2C%20always-quiet%20home%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20because%20we're%20usually%20pretty%20attached%20at%20the%20hip%2C%20it%20can%20feel%20more%20difficult%20to%20do%20things%20without%20each%20other.%20This%20struggle%20is%20both%20emotional%20and%20practical.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETake%20one%20time%20last%20spring%2C%20for%20example%2C%20when%20Sean%20met%20a%20coworker%20for%20lunch.%20I%20stayed%20home%20%E2%80%A6%20except%20%26quot%3Bhome%2C%26quot%3B%20in%20this%20case%2C%20was%20inside%20our%20van%20in%20the%20restaurant's%20parking%20lot.%20Yeah%2C%20it%20felt%20a%20little%20weird.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a6e2cc0b-4988-4f22-b53a-c648ecd41fcc%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe're%20closer%20than%20before%2C%20literally%20and%20figuratively%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20writer%20and%20her%20boyfriend%20standing%20in%20front%20of%20a%20glacier%20on%20a%20boat.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69ab0bb7d3e2f1aef36a22ba%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221190%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3Ecaptiontk%3Cp%3EHaley%20Young%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20us%2C%20the%20greatest%20risk%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-into-tiny-house-became-minimalist-declutter-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eliving%20in%20a%20small%20space%3C%2Fa%3E%20isn't%20finding%20ourselves%20at%20each%20other's%20throats%2C%20but%20becoming%20codependent.%3C%2Fp%