ffrey-epstein-files-bad-grammar-spelling-trump-ellison-dorsey-gates-thiel-cbfe9fb1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWall%20Street%20Journal%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20place%20that%20employs%20editors%20to%20do%20more%20than%20just%20catch%20typos%2C%20wrote%20about%20how%20the%20rich%20and%20powerful%20are%2C%20in%20some%20cases%2C%20abandoning%20perfect%20prose.%20The%20examples%20they%20cite%20include%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fblock-lay-off-4000-employees-read-jack-dorseys-memo-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EJack%20Dorsey's%20all-lowercase%20memo%3C%2Fa%3E%20announcing%20layoffs%20at%20Block%20and%20David%20Ellison%20texting%20David%20Zaslav%20and%20somehow%20writing%20their%20shared%20first%20name%20as%20%26quot%3BDaivd%26quot%3B%20(as%20someone%20who%20typos%20their%20own%205-letter%20name%20not%20unfrequently%2C%20I%20find%20this%20relatable).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20notable%20recent%20example%20of%20how%20the%20rich%20and%20powerful%20have%20abandoned%20the%20bourgeois%20veneration%20of%20proper%20writing%20is%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fepstein-files-reveal-how-billionaires-spend-money-mortimer-zuckerman-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EEpstein%20Files%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20are%20full%20of%20Jeffrey%20Epstein's%20awful%20typing%20in%20emails.%20Of%20course%2C%20Epstein%20isn't%20aspirational.%20Please%20do%20not%20mistake%20me%20here.%20But%20if%20you%20look%20at%20just%20his%20typing%20%E2%80%94%20and%20some%20of%20the%20replies%20he%20got%20from%20rich%20and%20powerful%20friends%20%E2%80%94%20you%20can%20gather%20my%20point%3A%20It%20seems%20that%20if%20you're%20rich%20and%20powerful%20enough%2C%20one%20of%20the%20many%20things%20people%20are%20willing%20to%20overlook%20is%20god-awful%20written%20communications.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20written%20before%20about%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.buzzfeednews.com%2Farticle%2Fkatienotopoulos%2Fi-tried-emailing-like-your-boss%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eemailing%20like%20a%20CEO%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20replying%20to%20emails%20immediately%2C%20often%20with%20just%20a%20few%20words%2C%20or%20sending%20a%20message%20with%20just%20a%20subject%20line%20and%20no%20body.%20For%20the%20most%20important%20person%20at%20a%20company%2C%20some%20of%20the%20pleasantries%20of%20formal%20email%20style%20aren't%20required.%20I%20even%20tried%20emailing%20like%20a%20CEO%20myself%20as%20an%20experiment.%20Hammering%20through%20my%20inbox%20like%20Paul%20Bunyan%20made%20me%20feel%20invigorated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20problem%20is%20that%20when%20you're%20not%20the%20boss%2C%20sending%20emails%20like%20a%20boss%20can%20come%20off%20as%20rude.%20Or%20maybe%20not%3F%20As%20the%20WSJ%20story%20points%20out%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3EDisregarding%20spelling%20and%20grammar%20in%20a%20written%20conversation%20can%20be%20a%20power%20move%20or%20a%20sign%20of%20friendliness%2C%20or%20perhaps%20both%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20said%20Deborah%20Tannen%2C%20a%20linguistics%20professor%20at%20Georgetown%20University.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EIt%20conveys%3A%20%26quot%3BI'm%20important%2C%20you're%20not%20so%20I%20don't%20have%20to%20bother%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3BWe're%20so%20friendly%2C%20I%20don't%20have%20to%20worry%2C%20we%20don't%20stand%20on%20ceremony%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2280587d98-2a93-43b6-b9a0-a1a787f2cd52%5C%22%3EHandcrafted%20emails%20can%20show%20you're%20not%20AI%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20been%20a%20big%20change%20in%20written%20communication%20since%20I%20last%20tried%20emailing%20like%20a%20CEO%2C%20back%20in%202017.%20That's%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20tools%20have%20made%20super-polished%20text%20easy%20to%20produce%20for%20anyone%20%E2%80%94%20either%20because%20you%20used%20ChatGPT%20to%20completely%20write%20an%20email%2C%20or%20a%20tool%20like%20Grammarly%20to%20polish%20up%20your%20own%20writing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20general%2C%20giving%20more%20people%20access%20to%20well-written%20emails%20is%20a%20good%20thing.%20But%20in%20a%20world%20of%20perfect%20AI-written%20(or%20assisted)%20text%2C%20how%20do%20you%20stand%20out%3F%20How%20do%20you%20signal%20you're%20operating%20on%20a%20higher%20level%20than%20the%20%3Cem%3Ehoi%20polloi%3C%2Fem%3E%3F%20That's%20right%20%E2%80%94%20with%20typos.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETypos%2C%20sloppy%20grammar%2C%20and%20downright%20hostile%20capitalization%3A%20They're%20all%20signs%20of%20hand-crafted%2C%20AI-free%20writing.%20And%20when%20AI%20writing%20makes%20text%20cheap%2C%20the%20value%20of%20real%20writing%20goes%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20typo-free%20email%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworkslop-oozing-americas-white-collar-offices-generative-ai-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eworkslop%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Send%20an%20AI-assisted%20email%20with%20perfect%20prose%2C%20and%20the%20recipient%20feels%20you%20made%20no%20real%20effort.%20Send%20a%20bespoke%2C%20finger-typed%20email%2C%20and%20it%20shows%20you%20care%20enough%20to%20send%20your%20thoughts%20directly%20%E2%80%94%20without%20an%20AI%20filter.%20It's%20intimate%2C%20special%2C%20precious.%20Mistakes%20and%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20if%20you%20want%20to%20send%20a%20really%20important%20email%20to%20someone%2C%20make%20sure%20you've%20got%20a%20few%20typos%20in%20there.%20And%20tell%20'em%20%3Cem%3EKaite%3C%2Fem%3E%20sent%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-typos-became-new-status-symbol-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1773330394000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69b1d374a96e437d6eb82a84%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-typos-became-new-status-symbol-2026-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22CEOs%2